node.text: If your traps and neck take over from shoulders, or hamstrings and quads take over from glutes - or you generally have a hard time training a body part - I guarantee you're making one of these mistakes.

node.title: 2 reasons why you're not making progress

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eugene Teo on August 17, 2021 tagging @coacheugeneteo. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'GANBARU Ask me a question What are your top three values?'.

node.text: I've wanted to be able to sing ever since I was a kid, but never had confidence in my abilities. Even after getting private lessons for over a year, I'm still hesitant to put myself out there. But the other day I decided to suck it up, embrace being a beginner, and just share it. And y'all have been so supportive ever since 🥺🙏

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Eugene Teo on August 17, 2021 tagging @coacheugeneteo. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'GANBARU Ask me a question What are your top three values?'.

Photo by Eugene Teo on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'GANBARU I. Honesty Be brutally honest always. We usually justify lies by saying it's to protect other people's interests or feelings, when in reality it's to protect yourself from being vulnerable to other people potentially not accpting your authentic self. It takes courage to be honest. Do what's right, not what's easy.'.

Photo by Eugene Teo on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'GANBARU 2. Ownership No one is coming to save you. You are responsible for every decision/non decision you make, and the consequences that come with it. Similarly, you can't own another person's decisions, or control their outcomes. Own what you are responsible for, and walk away from what you aren't responsible for. Fiercely.'.

Photo by Eugene Teo on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'GANBARU 3. Empathy Always do your best to consider things from the other person's perspective. What must life be like for them? Why do they hold the views they do? Why do they act the way they do? More often than not, people tend to act out of fear which gets misinterpreted as personal slights or malice.'.

node.text: Back training 101. One thing I always admired about John was his ability to simplify concepts. No fancy jargon, no pretentious waffle. Just basic, direct and easy to digest information. @mountaindog1

node.text:
Thank you for believing in me long before anyone else did.

Thank you for teaching me what really matters in life.

Thank you for all the memories, the support and most of all, your friendship.

RIP to the greatest friend a guy could ever have.
@mountaindog1

node.text:
30 today 🥳
Thank you all for the fun memories over the past year. It might seem strange to say it, but most of my happiest moments, whether it's in work, relationships or something in between, have come directly the connections I've created on here.

And thank you to everyone who peer pressured me into buying the most beautiful guitar in all the land for it. Here's the first song that made me want to start playing when I was about 6 years old.

node.text:
This is Sharelle. She’s been my training partner since late 2019 after she said hi to me at the gym and mentioned she was a Ganbaru member. Since then, she’s become one of my closest friends as we systematically try to crush each other’s souls in the gym, and push each other to level up out of the gym.

We keep each other accountable, call each other out and help each other grow. I’ve watched her transition into the coaching space, growing her brand and becoming one of the best coaches and role models in the female space - and one of the few that I’d ever trust to program for me.

And that’s exactly what I asked her to do for me - Sharelle has just launched a full 12 week program on Ganbaru Method, so you can join in and see what all the fuss is about. There’s currently a sale running on memberships for access to her program and ALL other content on the app. Link in bio.

#NotMyGirlfriend
#SeriouslyShesNotMyGirlfriend
#StopAskingIfShesMyGirlfriend
#WhyHaventYouSignedUpToGanbaruYet
@sharellegrant
